{"count": 28684, "next": "https://api.acmi.net.au/creators/?page=1689", "previous": "https://api.acmi.net.au/creators/?page=1687", "results": [{"id": 28891, "name": "Hugo Fregonese", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2183347, "title": "Decameron nights", "work_id": 86947, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1908-04-08", "date_of_death": "1987-01-11", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 5, "name": "German", "slug": "german"}, {"id": 10, "name": "Spanish", "slug": "spanish"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 23, "name": "Argentina", "slug": "argentina"}], "biography": "Hugo Geronimo Fregonese (April 8, 1908 in Mendoza – January 11, 1987 in Tigre) was an Argentine film director and screenwriter who worked both in Hollywood and his home country.He made his directorial debut in 1943. In 1949, he directed Apenas un delincuente. Most of Fregonese's American films were Westerns and crime melodramas, like Man in the Attic (1953) and Black Tuesday (1954). He worked with worldwide renowned actors such as Gary Cooper, Barbara Stanwyck, Anthony Quinn, Edward G. Robinson, Luisa Vehil, Víctor Laplace, Soledad Silveyra, Paul Naschy, and Joel McCrea, among others.\nFor directing the now-almost forgotten film My Six Convicts (1952), Fregonese was nominated for the Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing - Feature Film.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T11:46:48.530212+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2249, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugo_Fregonese"}], "uuid": "85a13b02-a7e7-4b0f-b406-1f64e10ea817", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "20698", "external_references": [{"id": 9660, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q321089"}, {"id": 9661, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "71599378"}, {"id": 9662, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "nr98038574"}, {"id": 9663, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-nr98038574"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:30:03.111514+10:00"}, {"id": 28890, "name": "M Frankovich", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 1998028, "title": "The Shootist [DVD]", "work_id": 93588, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2183344, "title": "Decameron nights", "work_id": 86947, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T14:56:32.049867+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "5f468374-eca1-46dc-a544-9f75fd0891ba", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "24162", "external_references": [{"id": 52156, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121357852"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T22:35:36.360862+10:00"}, {"id": 28889, "name": "Jean-Pierre Melville", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3105069, "title": "L'armee des Ombres = the Shadow Army", "work_id": 116230, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2121867, "title": "Bob the gambler = Bob le flambeur", "work_id": 92475, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3105229, "title": "Le Doulos = the Finger Man", "work_id": 116310, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3105227, "title": "Leon Morin, Pretre = Leon Morin, Priest", "work_id": 116309, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104787, "title": "Le Silence de la Mer = the Silence of the Sea", "work_id": 116081, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104668, "title": "Bob le Flambeur = Bob the Gambler", "work_id": 116025, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 811363, "title": "The Unmanageable children = Les enfants terribles", "work_id": 92441, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "Jean-Pierre Grumbach", "date_of_birth": "1917-10-20", "date_of_death": "1973-08-02", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 4, "name": "French", "slug": "french"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 17, "name": "France", "slug": "france"}], "biography": "Jean-Pierre Melville (French: [mɛlvil]; born Jean-Pierre Grumbach; 20 October 1917 – 2 August 1973) was a French filmmaker and actor. Among his films are Le Silence de la mer (1949), Le Doulos (1962), Le Samouraï (1967), Army of Shadows (1969) and Le Cercle Rouge (1970).\nWhile with the French Resistance during World War II, he adopted the pseudonym Melville as a tribute to his favorite American author Herman Melville. He kept it as his stage name once the war was over. Spiritual father of the French New Wave, he has influenced new generations of filmmakers in Asia (John Woo, Ringo Lam, Johnnie To, Takeshi Kitano), in Europe (Aki Kaurismäki, Rainer Werner Fassbinder), and in America (Michael Mann, Walter Hill, Quentin Tarantino, William Friedkin, Jim Jarmusch).", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T11:55:21.480408+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2346, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Pierre_Melville"}], "uuid": "9e069fb0-0018-43c3-8425-05fdfc41fb2c", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "21617", "external_references": [{"id": 10062, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q168693"}, {"id": 10063, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "68978193"}, {"id": 10064, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n50007876"}, {"id": 10065, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n50007876"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T23:00:42.382006+10:00